* Round 2: Coding Assessment

The shortlisted candidates will then appear for a proctored coding assessment that will consist of
3 questions to be attempted in 90 minutes, covering languages like Python, Java, C, C++ etc.. The
scores will be calculated based on the clearance of test cases for these questions, and the ones
which are equal to or higher than the cutoff score will move to the next round.

* Round 3: Case Study-based Code

The shortlisted candidates will receive a business problem statement of Flipkart and will be asked
to solve the same through Tech. This will require you to build a tool or system level solution for the
proposed problem, and share the code for the same. The detailed brief of the round will be given
to the relevant participants when the round will go live.

* Round 4: National Finals

The Top 48 candidates will be selected for the grand finale round, and will be invited to the Flipkart
Headquarters in Bangalore, for the final evaluation. The selected candidates will be asked to form
teams of 4, develop a prototype based on the solutions submitted by them in the previous round,
and come prepared with a live demo of the working prototype. The Flipkart leadership jury will
evaluate them based on the same, and the top 6 teams (24 candidates) will be awarded. The
detailed brief of the round will be given to the relevant participants when the round will go live.

Hiring Process:

Post round 3, subject to clearance of collated evaluation score of the submission, and based on
the year of study, the candidates will be shortlisted for either summer internship, winter
internship, or full-time opportunities. The details of the process will be shared at a later stage for
the relevant participants via their respective platforms.
